C               473
C               1128
C               242
C               475
</code></pre></div><p>We want to determine how the three vaccines perform c=
ompared to each other. This can be quantified by determining if each vaccin=
e causes the recipients to produce the same number of antibodies. Essential=
ly we are looking to determine if the antibody data for each vaccine origin=
ates from the same distribution. We have relatively small sample sizes so w=
e cannot well-determine if the data is normally distributed, so we use the =
Kruskal-Wallis test.</p><h3>Step 1:</h3><p>Null Hypothesis <span><span clas=
